## PART2 Antoine equation ##
options(repos="https://cran.rstudio.com" )

setwd("C:\\Users\\user\\Downloads")
antoine<-read.csv("antoine.csv")
t<-antoine[,2]
p<-antoine[,3]

#a#
par(mfrow=c(1,3))
plot(t,p)
plot(t,log(p))
plot(1/t,log(p))

#b#
#method1)
c<-c(-10,0,10,20,30,40,50)
s<-NULL
for(i in 1:7){
  x<-t-c[i]; x1<-1/x
  lm1<-lm(log(p) ~ x1)
  s[i]<-sqrt(sum(residuals(lm1)^2)/11)
}
which.min(s) # c=40일 때 최소
## [1] 6
x<-1/(t-40)
lm(log(p)~x) # a=23.12, b=-3961.22
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = log(p) ~ x)
## 
## Coefficients:
## (Intercept)            x  
##       23.12     -3961.22
theta<-c(23.12,-3961.22,40)
g.optim<-theta[1]+theta[2]/(t-theta[3])
sigsq<-sum((log(p)-g.optim)^2)/10  #0.0002943667
rm(theta)

#method2)
#step1
x1<-1/t
x2<-log(p)/t
lm(log(p)~x1+x2)
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = log(p) ~ x1 + x2)
## 
## Coefficients:
## (Intercept)           x1           x2  
##       23.16     -4891.55        39.22
alpha<-23.16
beta<- -4891.55
gamma<-39.22

init<-c(alpha,beta+alpha*gamma,gamma)
init   #(23.16,-3983.215,39.220)
## [1]    23.160 -3983.215    39.220
#step2
X<-matrix(0,13,3)
fun<-function(a,b,c){
  X[,1]<-1
  X[,2]<-1/(t-c)
  X[,3]<-b/(t-c)^2
  g<-a+b/(t-c)
  z<-as.matrix(log(p)-g,13,1)
  beta.hat<-solve(t(X)%*%X)%*%t(X)%*%z
  return(beta.hat)
}

add.beta<-fun(init[1],init[2],init[3])
theta<-init
for(j in 1:10){
  add.beta<-fun(theta[1],theta[2],theta[3])
  theta<-theta+add.beta
}

#step3
g.optim<-theta[1]+theta[2]/(t-theta[3])
sigsq<-sum((log(p)-g.optim)^2)/10  #0.0002826602

# R - non linear regression

nls1<-nls(log(p)~a+b/(t-c),start=list(a=init[1],b=init[2],c=init[3]))
summary(nls1)$parameters[,1]
##           a           b           c 
##    23.17154 -3992.47065    38.89796
(summary(nls1)$sigma)^2
## [1] 0.0002826602
## PART3 Mark - Recapture ##
options(repos="https://cran.rstudio.com" )
setwd("C:\\Users\\user\\Downloads")
#a#
mark<-read.csv("mark.csv")[1:37,]
L1<-mark[,5]
L2<-mark[,6]
gap<-mark[,4]

y<-L2
x<-L1
t<-gap/365.25

#Gurlland and Holt method
Lm<-apply(cbind(L1,L2),1,mean)
deriv<-(L2-L1)/t
lm(deriv~Lm)$coef
## (Intercept)          Lm 
## 115.1823858  -0.4077733
alpha<-lm(deriv~Lm)$coef[1]  #115.1823858
beta<-lm(deriv~Lm)$coef[2]   #-0.001116

#non linear regression
L<- -alpha/beta  #initial L = 282.4667
k<- -beta        #initial k = 0.4077733
nls2<-nls(y~a-(a-x)*exp(-b*t),start=list(a=L,b=k))
summary(nls2)   #L=283.35924, k=0.36077, sigma=11.37
## 
## Formula: y ~ a - (a - x) * exp(-b * t)
## 
## Parameters:
##    Estimate Std. Error t value Pr(>|t|)    
## a 283.35855   11.06552  25.607  < 2e-16 ***
## b   0.36077    0.05842   6.175 4.54e-07 ***
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
## 
## Residual standard error: 11.37 on 35 degrees of freedom
## 
## Number of iterations to convergence: 3 
## Achieved convergence tolerance: 9.704e-06
L.hat=283.35924; k.hat=0.36077

#b#
t0<-log((L.hat-51.5)/L.hat)/k.hat
tt<-seq(0,30,by=0.1)
Lt<-L.hat*(1-exp(-k.hat*(tt-t0)))
par(mfrow=c(1,1))
plot(tt,Lt,type="l",main="Growth Curve",xlab="t (시간)",ylab="growth (성장길이)",lwd=3,col="dark blue")
abline(h=51.5,lty=2); text(4,70,"출생시 평균길이 = 51.5",cex=1)
abline(h=L.hat,lty=2); text(25,275,"최대길이=283.35")
